JD 1 

Tasks
 

Develop and execute category strategies for FMCG products (both food and non-food).
Analyze market trends, competitor activities, and consumer behavior to identify growth opportunities.
Manage product assortment, pricing, promotions, and inventory levels.
Collaborate with sales, marketing, and supply chain teams to achieve category objectives.
Build and maintain strong relationships with suppliers and vendors.
Monitor category performance and report on key metrics.
Ensure optimal product placement and visibility within retail environments.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JD 2 :

- Category strategy and growth

- Build and execute robust business plans and long-term category strategy.

- Identify and capitalize on new market opportunities, trends, and customer needs.

- Define competitive go-to-market strategies to drive growth and differentiation.

- Own the category P&L, driving revenue, margins, market share and profitability.

Product and portfolio management:

- Continuously evaluate and refine the product portfolio for market relevance.

- Identify whitespace opportunities, collaborate on new product development and manage the complete product lifecycle.

Marketing and brand building:

- Collaborate to build 360 marketing campaigns ATL, BTL, digital, and influencer-led activities.

- Drive brand awareness, equity, and engagement across all consumer touchpoints.

- Collaborate with creative, media, and digital agencies on campaign development.

Consumer and market insights:

- Conduct consumer research to gather feedback for existing and new product launches.

- Translate insights into actionable strategies for communication and innovation.

Cross-functional collaboration:

- Work closely with the Sales Channel Teams, Operations Team and Marketing Team for strategy alignment and driving execution.

- Ensure marketing and brand initiatives are aligned with GTM and channel strategies.

