JD 17:

Key Responsibilities:

A. Category Development and Brand Onboarding:
Expand relevant categories in Quickcom B2B business
Channel agnostic approach while evolving categories and assortment
Drive AOV > INR 10000 (10x vs B2C QuickCom); Total Lines Sold per Order > 10
Help brands to drive non-KVI, new consumer demands, expand distribution

B. Deliver 3-5 Years GMV Plan
Develop long-term revenue plan on category and channel level
Lead Annual Business Plan, resulting into monthly S&OP Process with monthly category and brand wise GMV and CM1 Plan; and actualization
Monthly Brand wise P&L : Target to improve CM1 > 3% through better product mix, long-term favourable procurement deals, QPS, minimize inventory expiry

C. Supplier Relationship and Inventory Management:
TOT and long-term business collaboration with international, national, regional and D2C brands. Ensure negative working capital maintained
Operate with 3 days inventory level at every dark store
Ensure fill rate > 100% for KVI and 90% > for non-KVI

D. Customer Focus:
Defining and deploying Customer acquisition and retention strategy; regular tactical interventions to ensure weekly customer retention > 90%
Focus on repeat orders per day > 3 per customer
Champion a customer-centric approach in all buying decisions, ensuring products meet customer expectations and preferences.
Utilize customer feedback and insights to refine product assortment and enhance the shopping experience.

E. Sales and Marketing Collaboration:
Preparing and deploying quarterly market activation calendar; and pre-align with brands on co-execution and monetization
Work closely with the sales and marketing teams to develop promotional strategies that drive product visibility and sales.
Coordinate with the merchandising team to ensure effective product placement and presentation.


